Zhang Guangjun was appointed as the vice governor of Guangdong Province.
The fifth meeting of the Standing Committee of the 13th National People's Congress of Guangdong Province held its second plenary meeting in Guangzhou on the 30th.
The meeting voted to appoint Zhang Guangjun as the deputy governor of the People's Government of Guangdong Province.
Previously, Zhang Guangjun was deputy secretary of the party committee of the China Academy of Engineering Physics.
Comrade Zhang Guangjun's resume: Zhang Guangjun, male, Han Chinese, born in February 1968, Chongqing, joined the party in April 1994, joined the party in July 1991, graduated in electronic instruments and measurement technology of the Department of Radio Engineering of Harbin University of Technology, university degree, senior engineer, and expert of the State Council government special allowance.
He is currently the vice governor of the Guangdong Provincial Government and a member of the party group.
1987-1991, Department of Radio Engineering, Harbin Institute of Technology, Electronic Instrumentation and Measurement Technology
1991-1998 Technical staff member, deputy director of the General Engineering Research Institute of the China Academy of Engineering Physics, secretary and deputy director of the party branch of the department
1998-2002 Deputy Director of the General Engineering Research Institute of the China Academy of Engineering Physics and Deputy Secretary of the Party Committee (during which: 1999.05-2000.12 also served as the Secretary of the Discipline Commission of the Research Institute, 2001.09-2001.12 Sichuan Provincial Party Committee Party School District Office-level cadre training course)
2002-2002 Party Secretary and Deputy Director of the Institute of General Engineering of the Chinese Academy of Engineering Physics (during which: 2002.03-2004.05 Postgraduate Course in Management Science and Engineering, Fudan University School of Management)
2002-2009 Director of the Political Department of the Chinese Academy of Engineering Physics, Director of the Office of the Party Committee, Vice-President of the Party School (during which: 2005.09-2006.01 Middle School of Young Cadres Training Course)
Director of the Major Special Management Office of the China Academy of Engineering Physics from 2009 to 2014 (during which: 2011.09-2012.01 Middle and Young Cadre Training Courses of the Central Party School)
