Adm. William Moran, undersecretary of command for the U.S. Navy, said that even as the U.S. Navy is revitalizing its power to deal with an increasingly worrisome Russia on both sides of the Atlantic, the United States continues to focus the Asia-Pacific region, which the Pentagon has expanded to include the Indo-Asia-Pacific.
According to the British "Jane's Defense Weekly" website reported on September 24, the United States listed China and Russia as strategic competitors in the new national defense strategy announced at the beginning of the year.
Since then, the U.S. Navy has resumed the Second Fleet in order to more directly counter Russian activities.
The moves have raised some questions and concerns among allies and analysts that the U.S. Navy could move away from the “Asia-Pacific rebalancing” strategy that marked the Obama administration.
But Admiral Moran said the U.S. Navy’s focus remains on the Western Pacific.
“For us, there have been no major changes,” he said at a roundtable discussion called “Responding to the Challenges of the High Seas,” hosted by the National Bureau of Asian Studies in Washington, D.C., on January 24, 2018.
“The focus is still on rebalancing, shifting the center of gravity, or how you want to describe it,” Moran says.
He acknowledged that the United States has close ties with Europe.
“We’re going to continue to focus on growth on the West Coast and balance what we can do,” he said.
While Moran pointed to the overall policy regarding Russia falls within the purview of the U.S. defense secretary, he warned: "Russians may face demographic and economic challenges, but history proves that they will be very tough if we clash with them."
As part of a renewed U.S. effort to counter Russia, China and other competitors, the U.S. Navy is dynamically deploying troops into a “new mode of operations,” which would help catch adversaries off guard against where U.S. carrier battle groups or other assets will be deployed at any given time and place, Admiral Moran said.
“We in the Navy and Marine Corps support it — the concept of operational unpredictability, not to be in the same place again and again, almost like a shipwork — that’s what we do,” he said.
The first to attempt this new approach was the Harry Truman carrier strike group, whose early deployment included working visits to ports and patrolling areas that were usually only through.
Moran said the U.S. Navy is working to ensure allies know that the ships will still patrol in traditional areas and is also addressing logistical and family liaison issues for the new deployment process.
The commander of the Royal Australian Navy, Lt. Gen. Michael Noonan, also spoke at the event, saying Australian troops could work seamlessly with U.S. carrier battle groups.
He said the situation would continue as the Royal Australian Navy plans to procure nine more frigates equipped with Aegis combat systems.
Since October 5, a number of airlines have raised or resumed fuel surcharges, and next Friday, the plane will have to increase the cost of travel.
Yesterday, Xiangpeng Airlines, Okay Airlines and other airlines announced that since October 5, 2018 (the ticket date), the domestic route fuel surcharge of 800 km (inclusive) per passenger will be charged a fuel surcharge of 20 yuan per passenger, and more than 800 kilometers of routes per passenger will charge a fuel surcharge of 30 yuan per passenger.
Xiangpeng Airlines, Aokai Airlines and other companies announced that since October 5, 2018, the standard for fuel surcharges on domestic routes of 800 kilometers (including) has increased from 10 yuan / person to 20 yuan / person, and the fuel surcharge on domestic routes above 800 kilometers has increased from 10 yuan / person to 30 yuan / person per passenger.
Children and military and police disabled are all 10 yuan / person; infants continue to be exempt.
According to the person in charge of Ctrip ticket, the airline has indicated in the notice that the charge for the fuel surcharge is based on the original ticket date, and when the ticket is exchanged, the fuel surcharge is not refunded.
This means that domestic airline tickets issued before October 5, if you want to change to October 5 (inclusive), do not have to pay the fuel surcharge according to the new standard.
Since June 5, 2018, Air China, China Eastern Airlines, HNA, Shanghai Airlines, Spring and Autumn Airlines, Shenzhen Airlines, Western Airlines, Aokai Airlines and other airlines have resumed charging the fuel surcharge on domestic routes that have been cancelled for three years, and the standard is 10 yuan / person.
This time, Xiangpeng Airlines and Okai Airlines took the lead in announcing the increase in fuel surcharges, and as of the press release, they have not yet seen the news that the four major domestic airlines have announced to follow up the adjustment.
It is also understood that the Hong Kong Civil Aviation Department stipulates that airlines can decide whether to charge fuel surcharges in November.
Cathay Pacific announced on September 27 that it will re-charge fuel surcharges on November 2.
Cathay Pacific’s website shows that all tickets issued or re-issued by Cathay Pacific and Cathay Dragon on or after November 2 will include fuel surcharges for long-haul flights to and from Hong Kong and the South West Pacific, North America, Europe, the Middle East and India, Africa with a fuel surcharge of $652 and short-haul flights for $146.
The fee applies to all ticket types, per segment, and is included in the ticket price of all Cathay Pacific direct sales channels.
On the eve of the 69th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, Premier Li Keqiang met with the new ambassadors of 29 countries and regions in the Great Hall of the People on the afternoon of the 30th.
Li Keqiang shook hands and had a cordial conversation with his ambassadors in China.
Li Keqiang welcomed the envoys to China to perform their duties, and asked them to convey their sincere greetings and good wishes to the leaders and people of various countries and relevant institutions.
Li Keqiang spoke positively of China's good relations with other countries and regions, stressing that China is committed to enhancing bilateral political mutual trust, deepening practical cooperation, and strengthening coordination and cooperation in international and regional affairs. He hoped that envoys would walk and see more, and make new positive contributions to the development of China's relations with their respective countries and regions in their new posts.
The Chinese Government stands ready to facilitate and support the envoys in the performance of their duties.
Li Keqiang pointed out that China adheres to the path of peaceful development and unswervingly promotes economic globalization.
This year marks the 40th anniversary of China's reform and opening up, and as the world's largest developing country, we are willing to achieve common development with other countries in further expanding opening up.
In the context of the rise of protectionism and unilateralism, we are willing to work with all parties to continue to consolidate and strengthen partnerships based on the principles of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit, promote docking development strategies, promote the "Belt and Road" construction and cooperation in the principle of joint consultation, joint construction and sharing, jointly safeguard multilateralism and free trade, jointly build an open world economy, and inject new impetus into the stable and balanced development of the world economy.
The envoys of various countries and institutions in China warmly congratulated the 69th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, conveyed the greetings of the leaders of their respective countries and institutions to the leaders of China's leaders and people, and expressed that China's development achievements have made remarkable achievements, and believed that further deepening reform and opening up in the future will bring more development opportunities to the world.
We are willing to play a positive role in promoting friendly cooperation between their respective countries and regions with China and better achieving mutual benefit and win-win results.
Subsequently, the ambassadors of various countries and institutions in China attended the National Day reception at the invitation of Li Keqiang.
State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi attended the event.
Japan's Itochu Corporation on Friday recognized $1.3 billion in impairment losses on Chinese CITIC shares in its investment, a write-down of its largest corporate investment deal due to trade tensions between China and the United States.
A man walks past the headquarters of Marubeni Co., Ltd. in Tokyo, Japan, in May 2016.
Marubeni said that the trade war hit its U.S. grain division Gao Hong, which has suspended financial transactions in agriculture.
Some Japanese heavy equipment manufacturers, telecommunications companies and other companies have warned about the impact of Sino-US trade frictions when they announced the latest results, and now these Japanese trading houses have joined the ranks.
The United States and China have imposed tariffs on hundreds of billions of dollars of each other's goods, and U.S. President Donald Trump has threatened to expand the tax to more than $500 billion of Chinese exports if the dispute is not resolved.
Tsuyoshi Hachimura, Itochu’s chief financial officer for business, said the trade dispute could have a bigger impact on the Chinese economy next year.
Ito Corporation and Thailand’s Bumble Group invested $10 billion in CITIC in 2015 and acquired a 20% stake.
Hachimura said Ito Corporation lost 144.3 billion yen ($1.3 billion) in respect of this part of the shareholding because it believed that CITIC's stock price would not recover in the near future.
Itochu Corporation maintained its profit forecast for the fiscal year ended March 31, 2019 at 500 billion yen.
China imposed a 25 percent import tariff on U.S. soybeans in July to counter Washington’s moves in the trade war.
"Our grain business has been hit by the U.S.-China trade friction," said Mr. Yan Hong, Chief Financial Officer of Marubeni.
He said that Gao Hong has stopped financial transactions in his own accounts since September.
Gao Hong spokesman Pat Burke said in a statement on Friday that the company's move is "restricted in accordance with internal policies and due to a lack of market opportunities."
He also said the suspension of financial transactions would not lead to a loss of jobs.
Marubeni kept its annual profit forecast of 230 billion yen unchanged, helped by pulp and paper and power generation.
Sumitomo Corporation on Thursday reported a 16 percent profit increase from April to September, stressing that "the outlook for U.S.-China trade problems have led to an uncertain future."
Mitsubishi Corporation on Friday raised its annual profit forecast to record levels, attributed to higher coking coal production and higher prices for commodities such as oil and coal.
Mitsubishi Corporation also announced a new business plan to increase its profit in the fiscal year ended March 31, 2022, from an estimated 64 billion yen this year to 900 billion yen ($7.98 billion).
Comprehensive report, the US midterm election voting has entered the countdown.
On November 4, President Trump and his Democratic opponents actively "taped the vote" from their core voters.
Both parties have pointed out that voter turnout will be the key to the right and right election.
According to reports, 48 hours before the popular vote in the United States, Trump was busy attending the campaign of Republican candidates, and former President Obama went to Indiana to stand on the platform of Joe Donnelly, the Democratic Senate candidate who was eager to choose, and shouted to the masses before the final appeal.
On Nov. 4, Trump went to May Hill, Georgia, to stand for Republican gubernatorial candidate Brian Kemp, saying, "You have to go to the polls on Tuesday, you have to vote."
"The contrast to this election could not have been clearer."
Voter enthusiasm has risen to a rare peak, with early voting in some states far more than usual.
Successive U.S. presidents face the first mid-term elections, and his party often has fewer seats in Congress.
According to a new poll released by the Washington Post and ABC News on the 4th, although the Democratic House of Representatives election still maintains an advantage, Republicans can benefit from economic evaluation and Trump's strict focus on border security.
Polls show that registered voters prefer Democratic House candidates more than Republicans, at 50 percent to 43 percent, but that's down from a 14 percentage point lead in August.
A separate poll by NBC and the Wall Street Journal also showed Democrats still lead Republicans by seven percentage points.
It is reported that Obama told the crowd on the occasion of Senator Donnoley's campaign: "When people don't tell the truth, when words no longer represent anything, it will inevitably have bad results.
Democracy cannot work when people lie on their own.”
"The only way to stop these Republicans is you and your vote."
Democrats face the most difficult election in the Senate in decades, with Republicans now hold more than half of the 51 seats.
But the House is more favorable, and Democrats need to win another 23 seats to control the 435-seat House of Representatives.
Analysts at FiveThirtyEight.com, a prediction campaign site, estimated the Democratic Party's chances of winning the House of Representatives by as much as 85 percent.
