BEIJING, Nov. 5 (Wang Xiaoyan) Under the current wave of "mass entrepreneurship and innovation", more and more technology companies have begun to attach importance to patent research and development and related protection work, dig deep into the potential value of patents, and occupy the market dominance.
Similarly, many technology companies have encountered a lot of infringement in terms of patent technology licensing and patent technology use.
At the end of 2017, Tan Wei, He Zhanghong and Lai Bin from Guangdong Province took the developer of "Didi Travel" APP Beijing Xiaoqing Technology Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Xiaoqi Technology), operator Didi Travel Technology Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Didi Chuxing), and the seller Guangdong Pacific Internet Information Service Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Guangdong Pacific) to the Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court.
The three plaintiffs requested the court to order that the three defendants immediately stop the act of manufacturing, selling, promising sales and using the plaintiff's patent.
On October 30, 2018, China Referee Documents Network announced the "First Instance Civil Ruling of Tan Wei, He Zhanghong and Beijing Xiaoqing Technology Co., Ltd. and Beijing Xiaoqing Technology Co., Ltd.", which disclosed the details of some cases of patent infringement that Didi Chuxing APP was sued.
The three plaintiffs believe that the patentee and inventor of the patent "carpooling service system and method based on mobile terminals", and the entire operation process of the "downwind" application in the "drop travel" APP corresponds to the technical scheme of the patent protection, which constitutes patent infringement.
However, during the court ruling, Xiaoqing Technology believes that Guangdong Pacific is not a qualified defendant, it only provided free download of the APP "drop travel" on the network, did not implement the patent method involved in the case, there is no direct or indirect infringement, should not be listed as the defendant in this case.
Second, the violation in this case is not in Guangdong.
According to the law, the infringement of the patent involved should be the place where the patent method involved was fully implemented, so it objected to the jurisdiction of the court and asked to transfer the case to the defendant's residence court, the Beijing Intellectual Property Court.
The Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court held that the defendant Guangdong Pacific provided the accused of infringing Didi Travel APP products on its online platform, and it was not inappropriate for the plaintiff to list the defendant Guangdong Pacific as a defendant.
And the defendant Guangdong Pacific domicile is in Guangzhou City, which belongs to the jurisdiction of the Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court.
The defendant Xiaoqing Technology advocated the transfer of the case to the Beijing Intellectual Property Court for trial, and rejected the defendant Xiao Tang Technology Co., Ltd.'s objection to the jurisdiction of the case, and bear the cost of the acceptance of the jurisdictional case.
At present, other cases of the case have not yet been announced, and the reporter will pay close attention to the follow-up details of the patent infringement case of Didi Chuxing.
Interview with the Chief Executive Officer of the Australian Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organization: Australia-China scientific and technological cooperation has achieved remarkable results
"China's science and technology have developed rapidly in the past few decades, and Australia and China can achieve fruitful results in hand in the field of science."
Larry Marshall, CEO of the Australian Federal Scientific and Industrial Research Organization, said in an interview with China News Agency in Beijing that from the cooperation of climate change to the "eye of heaven" project, Australia and China's cooperation in the field of science and technology has shown vitality.
As the largest national scientific research institution in the Commonwealth of Australia, CSIRO has achieved many innovative research results in the fields of ocean, energy, biology, materials, astronomy and other fields.
CSIRO has maintained close cooperation with scientific research institutions such as the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
“It was an enduring friendship that included a tradition of trust in our partners and long-term cooperation,” Marshall said.
In May this year, China's 500-meter-caliber spherical radio telescope, the "China Eye", installed the world's first 19-beam L-band receiver.
At present, the most advanced 19 beam feeder receiver in the world is jointly developed by Chinese and Australian scientists.
Marshall said that the successful development of the receiver is based on the years of CSIRO technology accumulation, after the launch, the FAST survey speed will be increased by 5 to 6 times, at the same time, will also expand more scientific observation targets.
“This is a contribution of CSIRO to FAST.”
In addition to the above cooperation, CSIRO also cooperates closely with Chinese scientific research institutions in building square kilometers array radio telescopes, developing new fuel technologies, and energy conservation and emission reduction.
"In the past, scientific research has often focused on the problems of hundreds of years later, and now more scientific research forces are needed to solve the problems in front of them."
Marshall believes that Australia and China are complementary in the field of scientific development, and both countries face a series of challenges in their development.
For example, extreme weather is frequent around the world, droughts and floods have led to food production, and food shortages have seriously affected human development.
At the same time, the population explosion, aging, chronic diseases and other issues are also currently facing serious challenges.
"Australia-China cooperation in recent years is mainly focused on solving these current problems."
Marshall said that the focus of the International Southern Hemisphere Marine Research Center jointly established by CSIRO and Qingdao National Laboratory of Marine Science and Technology is to observe the El Niño phenomenon and La Niña phenomenon, study the relationship between the two and extreme weather, and establish an early warning facility for extreme weather; CSIRO and the Chinese Academy of Sciences jointly developed a new variety of grains to overcome extreme weather can also alleviate the food shortage caused by extreme weather.
"In the current environment, scientific and technological innovation is difficult to complete alone, the need for extremely high costs, to solve a lot of problems, so cooperation is particularly important today."
Marshall said that the closer the cooperation, the more likely it is to make breakthroughs, which is also the significance of Australia and China to strengthen cooperation under the framework of the Belt and Road Initiative.
"Strengthening bilateral cooperation is mainly for us in science and technology cooperation."
Marshall said, for example, CSIRO's latest development of a cyanide-free gold purification method, because the traditional cyanide gold purification method is very harmful to the environment, many countries hope to find a way to purify gold with small environmental pollution.
"We are very willing to introduce this technology to China, which is one of the results of our participation in the Belt and Road cooperation."
