North Korean Foreign Minister Ri Yong-ho told the United Nations on Saturday that continued sanctions were deepening North Korea's distrust of the United States, and it was impossible for North Korea to unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons under such circumstances.
Lee told the U.N. General Assembly that North Korea had taken a "very friendly approach" over the past year, including halting missile and nuclear tests, dismantling nuclear test sites and committing to the non-proliferation of nuclear weapons and technology.
“But we don’t see any corresponding response from the United States,” he said.
"If we don't trust the United States, we have no confidence in our national security, and in this case, we can't unilaterally give up our weapons first."
While Mr. Ri is repeating North Korea’s complaints about U.S. opposition to “phased” denuclearization, his speech is significant because it has not completely rejected unilateral denuclearization, as North Korea has done before.
Ri Yong-ho referred to Kim Jong-un and Trump’s June 12 joint statement, when Kim agreed to work on the “denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula” and Trump promised to protect North Korea’s security.
North Korea has sought to formally end the 1950-53 Korean War, but the United States says it must give up its nuclear weapons first.
The United States has also refused to ease international sanctions on North Korea.
"The United States insists on 'denuclearizing first', and increases sanctions pressure to achieve its goals in a high-pressure manner, and even refuses to issue a 'Declaration to End the War'," Li said.
“The idea that sanctions can make us kneel and ask for forgiveness is that people who don’t know us are daydreaming.
But the problem is that these persistent sanctions are deepening our mistrust.”
Lee did not mention the second special summit plan the U.S. president mentioned earlier this week at the United Nations.
Instead, he highlighted three meetings between Kim and South Korean President Moon Jae-in over the past five months, saying, “If the other side of the denuclearization is South Korea, not North Korea, then the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula will not become so deadlocked.”
China has reduced import tariffs on 1,585 tariff lines from November 1, 2018.
Since the beginning of this year, China has taken the initiative to reduce import tariffs.
On May 1 this year, the drug tariff reduction was comprehensively reduced, and the import tariffs on 28 tax items, including anti-cancer drugs, all ordinary drugs and alkaloids with anti-cancer effects and actual imports of Chinese medicine, were adjusted to zero.
At the same time, it has also greatly reduced the value-added tax burden on the production and import of anti-cancer drugs.
On July 1, taxes were reduced on 218 vehicles and parts.
After the tax reduction, China's automobile vehicle tax rate has been lower than the average of developing countries, which is in line with the actual situation of China's automobile industry.
This tax reduction will promote the adjustment of industry structure and the optimization of resource allocation, accelerate the survival of the fittest, help improve the quality of products and services, and is expected to promote the adjustment of automobile prices to a certain extent, so that consumers can get more benefits.
On July 1, taxes were reduced on consumer goods for 1,449 tax items.
The tax reduction of consumer goods is closely related to the needs of the people for a better life.
The tax reduction is not only a large number but also a large amount, the average tax reduction rate of 56%.
The reduction of taxes on consumer goods directly benefits the majority of consumers and promotes the competitiveness of domestic industries.
On November 1, tax reduction will be implemented for industrial products such as mechanical and electrical equipment, parts and raw materials for 1,585 tax items.
The appropriate reduction of import tariffs on some domestic urgently needed industrial products can attract more foreign investment, which is conducive to increasing domestic effective supply and helping industrial upgrading, while helping enterprises to allocate resources on a global scale, reduce production costs, and also help reduce the pressure carried by the domestic environment.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council of the People's Republic of China, the above four independent tax reductions, as well as the third step of tariff reduction implemented on July 1 this year, will reduce China's total tariff level from 9.8% last year to 7.5%.
The adjusted overall tariff level is slightly higher than that of the EU, lower than that of most developing countries, and at a moderately low level, which basically matches the status and development stage of China's developing country.
The person in charge introduced that the overall level of tariffs, as one of the important indicators of the openness of China's trade in goods, should be compatible with China's economic development stage and reflect the characteristics of the times.
China's trade in goods is the first in the world, and it already has the economic foundation for further opening up, but there is still a gap between the quality and efficiency of trade development and the developed economies, so the overall tariff level should be appropriately reduced.
Tariff is a means of protection for compliance, and the level of tariffs should be compatible with industrial competitiveness, encouraging healthy competition, and excessive protection is not conducive to industrial development and improving quality.
The adjustment of tariff rates should take into account the needs of production and consumption.
Focus on reducing the export rate of goods with large domestic demand and conducive to industrial transformation and upgrading, and strive to increase the import of characteristic and advantageous products with concentrated needs of the people, continuously enhance the sense of enterprise and public access, and meet the upgrading needs of industrial structure and consumption structure.
Tax reduction should take into account the affordability of fiscal revenue and industrial development.
In the selection of specific tax reduction commodities and tax reduction amplitude, it is necessary to coordinate and coordinate the two markets at home and abroad, the upstream and downstream aspects, and the two relations between production and consumption, and maintain the steady and good development momentum of China's economy.
The person in charge stressed that this year is the 40th anniversary of reform and opening up, and China's initiative to reduce the overall level of import tariffs is a major measure made according to China's own high-quality development needs, which is conducive to the overall utilization of international and foreign resources, promote the quality improvement of the domestic supply system, and meet the needs of the people's consumption upgrading.
This action and measure shows that China will unswervingly pursue an open strategy of mutual benefit and win-win results, firmly support economic globalization, firmly uphold the principle of free trade and the multilateral trading system with the WTO as the core, continue to draw development momentum from opening up to the world, and let China's development benefit the world better.
Serbia announces top readiness, president of Serbia to meet tomorrow to discuss Kosovo
According to the office of the Serbian president, in view of the Kosovo special forces occupying the passage of the gasivauda hydropower station in northern Kosovo controlled by Belgrade, Serbian President Vucic ordered the country's armed forces to enter the highest state of readiness.
On September 29, Serbian Defense Minister Vulin declared that the Serbian army had entered a state of full combat readiness.
Wulin stressed that as long as the order issued by Vucic remains in force, Serbia will continue to monitor the current situation in Kosovo, and the Serbian army will respond no matter which direction the situation is moving in.
According to Russia's TASS news agency, on September 29, Vucic said in an interview that he has briefed the United States, Russia and Europe on the current situation, and will travel to Moscow on October 2 to meet with Russian President Putin to seek Putin's support on the Kosovo issue.
Asked if Serbia needed Russia's military support, as in Syria, Vucic replied in a negative way: "I don't want a major military conflict on our territory."
Vucic also said that the Serbian army has entered a state of full-scale combat readiness only to form a deterrent to prevent the conflict from happening, but it is also a clear warning: no violence in Kosovo will be tolerated.
The reason why the army has improved its combat readiness is related to the two major actions on the Kosovo side.
According to the Serbian side, in recent days, Albanians have been mass-arresting Serbs living in the northern region of Kosovo for generations, and these arrested Serbs have not violated any law.
Vucic said that since March 26 this year, the head of the Serbian government's Kosovo and Metohija office, Makojuč, was beaten and detained by the Kosovo Albanian army, the Albanians have escalated the situation in the region, and the Serbs have been nevolently arrested and expelled.
In addition, more than 100 people, including the ROSU special forces, armed police and snipers of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Republic of Kosovo, which had recently been self-declared, occupied positions near the reservoir of the Gaziboda Hydropower Station, entered the ecological and sports center near the levees in the northern part of the Kosovo region, and blocked all roads in the vicinity, which were originally controlled by the Serbian side.
Vucic pointed out that this military adventure in Kosovo was carried out at the instigation of the Western countries, and the Kosovo army's move did not inform the Serbian side in advance, in violation of the Brussels Agreement, Chapter IX, paragraph 1, and also in violation of UN Security Council resolution 1244 and the military-technical agreement between Serbia.
Vucic has spoken to NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg, criticizing the hypocrisy of Western countries on Kosovo.
The root cause of the current conflict is the centuries-old historical annoy between the two communities in Kosovo.
With regard to the affiliation of Kosovo, Serbs and Albanians have their own statements.
Serbia saw Kosovo as the birthplace and cultural cradle of the nation, because it established its most powerful state here in the 12th century, and the Albanians moved in in large numbers only after the Ottoman invasion and the Serbian army retreated from the north.
The Albanians insist that the Illyrians, the primitive tribes that lived in Kosovo in the 4-5th century BC, are the ancestors of the Albanians, and therefore Kosovo has been the territory of the Albanians since ancient times.
The subjective political division has resulted in fierce conflicts between different ethnic groups, religions and cultures, and has created a fierce confrontation between Serbs and Albanians in the Kosovo region.
In 1912, the Kosovo Albanians first declared the independence of Albania.
After the First World War, a large number of Albanians living in the Balkans moved to Turkey, the proportion of Serbs increased relatively, in the view of the Serbs "just to take back their own land" approach, but by the Albanians as "Great Serbism" plunder, the contradiction between the two families intensified.
Kosovo became the "powder keg" of the Balkans.
In 1999, an armed conflict between Albanian separatists in the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA) and the Serbian army and police led to the bombing of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, which is composed of Serbia and Montenegro, and the Kosovo War broke out.
On 17 February 2008, Kosovo unilaterally declared its independence from Serbia.
Since then, although there have been reports that Serbia will normalize relations with Kosovo and sign a global and legally binding agreement, due to historical national grievances and geopolitical constraints, the agreement, which is subject to the United States, Europe and Russia and other forces, has not been signed.
Just a month ago, Vucic made it clear for the first time that he advocated the separation of Serbs from Albanians in Kosovo, and once again made the contradiction between the two communities public.
Electricity communication is still interrupted, Indonesia earthquake and tsunami rescue is difficult
According to the Indonesian Disaster Relief Agency released figures in the early morning of the 30th, a strong earthquake and tsunami caused by the Donggala County in Central Sulawesi Province of the country on the 28th have killed 420 people.
Wilem Rampangilei, head of the Indonesian Disaster Relief Agency, said that the figure is only the preliminary statistics of Palu City, the capital of Central Sulawesi Province, about 80 kilometers from the epicenter, because of the lack of large-scale search and rescue machinery, many of the city's hotels, shopping malls, warehouses and other densely populated buildings damaged by the earthquake have not yet been searched and rescued.
On September 29, 2018, local time, a bridge damaged by the earthquake and tsunami collapsed into several sections on the Bar Road, Indonesia.
Due to the severe damage to power and communication facilities, the epicenter of the earthquake in Donggala County and the neighboring Xiji area are still "islands" that cannot be contacted, and the number of victims cannot be counted.
According to media reports, Indonesian Vice President Carla said the death toll could be in the thousands.
Power outages, communications, road disruptions, airport damage... rescue efforts after the earthquake and tsunami were difficult.
Due to power outages, some hospitals and rescue settlements in Palu rely on fuel to generate electricity.
Roads in and out of the city were blocked by landslides, and large transport vehicles, including tankers, were unable to enter, making fuel supplies very tight.
Indonesian Social Minister Agous said that due to road damage, the ministry's emergency relief supplies such as tents, mattresses, blankets, clothing, food and household kits from the neighboring provinces of South Sulawesi and Kolundalo provinces in the earthquake area have not yet arrived in the disaster area.
Disaster relief supplies transferred from the capital Jakarta are being transported to the disaster area via air transport aircraft.
In view of the damage to the tower and runway of Palu airport in the earthquake, in order to ensure safety and ensure rescue, all commercial flights have been grounded, and military aircraft carrying relief supplies and personnel have taken off and landed only.
Indonesia's Coordinating Minister for Political, Legal and Security Affairs, who directs the rescue in the earthquake area, called for the resumption of power supply and commercial flight services at the airport as soon as possible to ensure the operation of rescue agencies such as hospitals, so that more rescue workers and volunteers and aid materials can reach the disaster area.
On the 28th, a series of strong earthquakes occurred in Donggala County, Central Sulawesi Province, Indonesia, of which a 7.7-magnitude earthquake occurred at 17:02 local time, causing major disasters in Palu City, Donggala County and Xiji District.
