Experts from the national filmless cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities walked into the experimental field and listened to the presentation of the representative of the academician team of Yu Shuxun of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.
Shaya, Xinjiang, September 30 (Geng Dandan Wang Xiaojun) is located in Shaya County, Xinjiang, the filmless cotton planting test base, filmless cotton is happy, compared with the ground film cotton "not inferior", a cluster of snow-white cotton competing "open", hanging branches.
From September 27 to 28, the national filmless cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
The reporter learned at the observation meeting that the filmless cotton technology system with "China Cotton 619" and its supporting cultivation measures as the main body has initially achieved the goal of filmless cultivation in cotton fields, reducing the pollution of the cottonfields to the ecological environment and raw cotton, and making significant progress in comprehensive research and demonstration of film-free cotton.
Academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, famous cotton genetic breeder, and chief scientist of the cotton system of the national modern agricultural industry technology system, introduced the growth of filmless cotton to Zhou Guom, secretary of the Party Committee of Zhejiang University of Agriculture and Forestry.
"We developed a comprehensive filmless cotton technology can fully realize the use of film planting cotton, can completely solve the problem of residual film pollution, to achieve green cotton planting."
The Chinese Academy of Engineering academician Yu Shuxun introduced.
Xinjiang is China's most important cotton-producing region, according to the National Bureau of Statistics statistics, in 2017 Xinjiang cotton planting area of 35 million mu, accounting for 61% of the country's cotton area.
Since the introduction of land film into China in 1982, the filming area of various types of crops in Xinjiang has reached more than 50 million mu, and the annual use of land film is about 300,000 tons.
Among them, cotton film coverage rate reached 100%, cotton field film accounted for about 60% of Xinjiang's land film use.
Filmless cotton for measurement and production, cotton production can be fully achieved 320 kg to 350 kg per mu.
With the increasing input of the film in Xinjiang, the recovery rate of the residual film is low, the amount of residual film in the soil is gradually increasing, and the residual film causes a series of problems such as the destruction of soil structure, which seriously affects the sustainable development of agriculture.
The residual film not only causes serious pollution to the soil, but also has a great impact on the quality of cotton fiber.
At present, more than one-third of cotton fields in Xinjiang have been mechanized.
In 2017, Xinjiang's cotton harvest area was about 14 million mu.
In the process of cotton harvesting, a large amount of surface and cotton film is mixed with the broken film on the cotton, and the shredder in the raw cotton is difficult to remove in the raw cotton processing process, and it cannot be completely removed in the subsequent textile processing process, which seriously affects the quality of textile products.
On September 28, the national filmless cotton scene observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
In order to solve the cotton field membrane pollution, simplify cotton planting technology, improve the efficiency of cotton fields, Yu Shuxun led his team through 8 years, the implementation of "China Cotton 619" filmless cotton technology planting, for the green development of Xinjiang agriculture "add wings".
Yu Shuxun introduced, through innovative breeding new ideas, cultivate a special precocious, salt-resistant, low-temperature, abundant land cotton new line "China cotton 619".
"'Medium cotton 619' in the southern region of Xinjiang film-free cultivation conditions, to achieve film-free seeding machinery supporting, sowing depth improvement, film-free conditions under the dripping tube with shallow burial, suitable sowing density screening, reasonable chemical control and other supporting measures."
At present, Aksu, Kurle, Aral and other places have established filmless cotton demonstration bases, with a output of 4,800 kilograms per hectare.
Filmless cotton cultivation has achieved abundant production, savings, environmental protection, and comprehensive efficiency improvement.
Zhang Donghai, a agronomist of the Third Division of the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, said that through nearly six years of research and demonstration of filmless cotton cultivation technology, the output of filmless cotton seed cotton can be completely achieved by 320 kg to 350 kg per mu, and may even be higher.
"Fleet-free cotton cultivation technology promotion prospects are very large."
Zhang Donghai believes that at present, filmless cotton cultivation technology can completely solve the problem of soil residual film pollution, but there is still a certain gap between the economic benefits compared to the cultivation of the film.
"Cotton purchase price support will be conducive to future promotion."
Yu Shuxun said that in the next step, he and his team will continue to conduct in-depth research and large-scale promotion and application of filmless cotton, make the filmless cotton industry bigger and stronger, and completely solve the soil pollution caused by the film.
