The reporter learned from the Ministry of Finance on the 30th that the four departments of the Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the National Development and Reform Commission and the Ministry of Commerce recently jointly issued a notice that in order to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China, the profits distributed by foreign investors from China's resident enterprises are not levied for domestic direct investment for the application of the withholding income tax policy, and the projects encouraged by foreign investment are expanded to all projects and areas that are not prohibited from foreign investment.
This policy is implemented as of January 1, 2018.
The notice clearly states that foreign investors direct investment with profit, including equity investment behaviors such as capital increase, new construction, and equity acquisition by overseas investors to share profits, but does not include new, re-elevation, and acquisition of shares of listed companies other than qualified strategic investments.
Foreign investors can enjoy the policy of not collecting the withholding income tax but not actually enjoy it in accordance with the provisions, and may apply for the collection and enjoyment of the policy within three years from the date of actual payment of the relevant tax, and refund the tax paid.
Not only that, after foreign investors enjoy the prescribed no-for-expense income tax policy, the restructuring of the invested enterprise meets the conditions for special restructuring, and the actual tax treatment is carried out in accordance with the special restructuring, and can continue to enjoy the policy treatment of not collecting withholding income tax.
In order to ensure that the profits obtained by foreign investors are actually used for direct investment, the notice stipulates that the profits of foreign investors for direct investment are paid in cash, and the relevant funds are directly transferred from the account of the profit distribution enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or equity transferor, and shall not be rotated in other accounts at home and abroad before the direct investment; the profits of foreign investors for direct investment are paid in the form of non-cash in kind, marketable securities, etc.
The notice also requires the tax department to strengthen follow-up management in accordance with the law.
Foreign investors have enjoyed the policy of not collecting withholding income tax, and if the tax department's follow-up management verification does not meet the prescribed conditions, in addition to the corporate responsibility for profit distribution, it is deemed that the foreign investor fails to declare and pay corporate income tax in accordance with the provisions, and will be investigated for delaying tax payment in accordance with the law.
