Xinhua News Agency, Fuzhou, October 1 (Reporter Qiu Xiaoan) On October 1, the "Fujian Province High-speed Railway Safety Management Regulations" was officially implemented.
The regulations put forward that within 500 meters on both sides of the wires of the high-speed rail power line, it is forbidden to fly air objects such as kites, balloons, orifices, flying machines and small aircraft.
Provisions on the basis of the "Railway Law of the People's Republic of China" and "Regulations on Railway Safety Management" and other superstitious laws, according to the geographical and climatic characteristics of Fujian Province, supplementary provisions on the prohibition and restriction of high-speed rail safety, standardize the construction of construction along the high-speed rail, tree planting and other acts, further clarify the main body of high-speed rail supervision and supervision scope, and clarify the responsibilities and legal responsibilities of law enforcement supervision.
The regulations are in response to the frequent coastal winds in Fujian Province, and the light construction materials and light floats along the high-speed rail are blown into the high-speed rail to affect the safety of the situation, and it is stipulated that within 500 meters on both sides of the high-speed rail power line wire, it is forbidden to fly kites, balloons, porous lights, power umbrellas, aircraft and other airborne objects and small aircraft.
In addition, light objects such as plastic greenhouses, color steel plates, sunshades and other lightweight objects along the high-speed rail and low-altitude floats and plastic protective films produced during the construction process, all people or users should take reinforcement protective measures to prevent harm to the safety of high-speed railways.
In view of the characteristics of Fujian Province in hilly areas and high-speed railway tunnels, it is stipulated that the construction of mountain ponds, reservoirs, dykes, excavation rivers, canals, and wells may affect the safety of tunnels, such acts as building mountain ponds, reservoirs, and dykes, drilling wells, which may affect the safety of tunnels, and should seek the opinions of railway construction units or railway transportation enterprises.
At the same time, those who violate the relevant responsibilities of the "provisions" will be ordered by the public security organs to make corrections; if the circumstances are more serious, the unit shall be fined not less than 5,000 yuan but not more than 10,000 yuan, and a fine of not less than 200 yuan but not more than 500 yuan shall be imposed on the individual; if the circumstances are serious, a fine of not less than 10,000 yuan but not more than 30,000 yuan shall be imposed on the individual.
Where the loss is caused, it shall be liable for compensation according to law.
It is understood that with the rapid development of railway construction, the high-speed railway mileage of 200 kilometers per hour and above in Fujian Province has now reached 1516 kilometers, which has realized the city's express train, and it is expected that the speed of 200 kilometers per hour and above in Fujian will reach 2,150 kilometers per hour and above in the next five years.
The implementation of this provision will standardize the safety management of high-speed rail in Fujian Province, further implement the responsibilities of local government departments, coordinate railway and local forces, work together to ensure the safety of high-speed rail, and improve the safety prevention and control system of high-speed rail in Fujian Province.
