One confirmed case of human infection with H5N6 avian influenza in Guangdong Province
The Health Bureau said that according to the latest notification from the mainland health department, a human case of H5N6 bird flu has been confirmed in Guangdong Province.
The Health Department urged residents to avoid contact with birds and pay attention to personal and food hygiene.
According to the data, the patient is a 22-year-old male, now living in Baiyun District, Guangzhou, Guangdong Province; on September 25, he developed symptoms such as fever, was admitted to the hospital for treatment on September 26, and is currently in isolation in the hospital, and is in critical condition.
The patient had killed and ate live poultry before the disease.
Since April 2014, there have been confirmed cases of H5N6 avian influenza in Sichuan, Guangdong, Yunnan, Hubei, Hunan, Anhui and Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Regions.
The Health Bureau will continue to maintain close contact with the health departments of the country and neighboring regions and the World Health Organization to closely monitor the epidemic situation in various places and in Macao.
In order to prevent human infection with avian influenza, the Health Bureau calls on the public to pay attention to the following matters:
Avoid contact with birds or their secretions and excreta; if they are in contact, wash their hands immediately;
Do not buy or carry unquaranted birds.
Do not eat unripe poultry meat, internal organs, blood products and eggs;
Pay attention to personal hygiene and wash your hands frequently;
If you have fever, cough, difficulty breathing and other symptoms, you should wear a mask, go to the doctor as soon as possible, and detail the travel history and animal contact history to the doctor.
