The "Notice on Further Strengthening the Broadcasting and Management of Radio and Television Advertising" stipulates that when broadcasting advertisements in the middle of film and television dramas, the TV station must strictly abide by the provisions of the General Administration's 61st order: 2 commercial advertisements can be interpolated in each episode (45 minutes), each time should not exceed 1 minute and 30 seconds; the time of the prime time (19:00 to 21:00) can be broadcast one commercial advertisement per episode, the duration should not exceed 1 minute; when the advertisement is inserted, the advertising time should be prompted.
The notice also stipulates that radio and television broadcasting institutions should strictly review the qualifications and certificates of health information advertising such as medical, pharmaceutical, medical equipment, and health food, and resolutely prohibit the broadcast of sexual advertisements.
