China, Pakistan agree to complete the construction project of the Economic Corridor in a timely manner and accelerate the construction of Gwadar Port
China's foreign ministry said on Sunday that China and Pakistan had agreed to further consolidate and expand their economic ties.
China and Pakistan issued a joint statement on Sunday to further strengthen their strategic partnership.
The two sides reaffirmed their "commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor" and "oppose negative publicity against the CPEC".
China's foreign ministry said China and Pakistan would "strengthen practical cooperation in trade and investment, and enhance Pakistan's industrial capacity through joint ventures in priority areas, transfer of labor-intensive industries and cooperation with small and medium-sized enterprises."
According to the press release published on the website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the two sides agreed to complete the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor in a timely manner, accelerate the construction of ports and supporting projects in Gwadar Port, focus on economic and social development, job creation and improvement of people's livelihood, and accelerate cooperation in industry and parks and agriculture.
"The two sides agreed to complete the second phase of the China-Pakistan Free Trade Agreement negotiations as soon as possible and continue to advance the negotiation of the China-Pakistan Trade Agreement on Trade in Services."
In the joint statement signed on Sunday, the two sides reaffirmed their commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor (CPEC) and agreed that the CPEC is a win-win cooperation plan that will promote regional connectivity and bring prosperity and development to the entire region.
The two sides agreed that the Gwadar Port is an important node for cross-regional connectivity and a pillar of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.
The two sides agreed to accelerate the construction of the port and supporting projects in Gwadar Port.
China and Pakistan also said in a joint statement that they opposed negative publicity against the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.
The two sides agreed to establish a strategic dialogue between the two foreign ministers and adjust the original strategic dialogue at the deputy foreign minister level to diplomatic consultations.
In addition, the two countries will further strengthen defense cooperation and maintain high-level visits and exchanges between various departments and levels of the two militaries.
In order to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China, the Ministry of Finance and other four ministries and commissions jointly informed that since January 1, 2018, the profits distributed by foreign investors from Chinese resident enterprises for domestic direct investment are not subject to the scope of application of the withholding income tax policy, and the foreign investment incentive projects have been expanded to all projects and areas that are not prohibited from foreign investment.
According to the relevant notice published on the website of the Ministry of Finance, foreign investors must meet several conditions at the same time, including direct investment by foreign investors to share profits, including equity-based investment by overseas investors to share profits, capital additions, new construction, equity acquisitions and other equity investment behaviors, but excluding new, re-elevation, and acquisition of shares of listed companies (except for qualified strategic investments).
Also included is the profits of overseas investors, which belong to the dividends, dividends and other equity investment income formed by the actual distribution of retained income realized by domestic resident enterprises in China to investors.
And the profits of foreign investors for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds are directly transferred from the account of the profit distribution enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or equity transferor, and shall not be in other accounts at home and abroad before the direct investment; the profits of the foreign investors for direct investment are paid in the form of non-cash in kind, securities, etc. The ownership of the relevant assets is transferred directly from the profit distribution enterprise to the invested enterprise or equity transferor, and shall not be held by other enterprises or individuals on behalf of or temporarily held before the direct investment.
The notice also said that foreign investors through equity transfer, repurchase, liquidation and other means to actually recover the direct investment to enjoy the suspension of withholding income tax policy treatment, within 7 days after the actual collection of the corresponding funds, in accordance with the prescribed procedures to file a payment of deferred taxes.
In order to encourage foreign investors to continue to invest and operate in China, the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Commerce and other four ministries and commissions jointly issued a notice at the end of 2017, since January 1, 2017, the profits distributed by foreign investors from Chinese resident enterprises directly invested in incentive investment projects, and if they meet the prescribed conditions, the deferred tax policy is implemented, and no withholding income tax is temporarily exempted.
The executive meeting of the State Council of China decided last week to expand the scope of application of foreign reinvestment tax on withholding from encouraging foreign-funded projects to all non-prohibited projects and fields, and further strengthen the protection of intellectual property rights.
The reporter learned from the National Health Commission that compared with a few decades ago, the incidence of malnutrition among children and adolescents in China has decreased, but the incidence of overweight and obesity has increased significantly.
Experts pointed out that to maintain a healthy weight, the most important concept is "cure the disease", vigorously promote scientific fitness, reasonable diet.
According to the "China Youth Health Education Core Information and Interpretations (2018 Edition)" recently released by the National Health and Health Commission, the key to maintaining a healthy weight is reasonable diet and scientific exercise.
Being overweight, obese and blindly losing weight are not good for health.
The health risks behind the "little fat pier" cannot be ignored.
Ding Gangqiang, director of the Nutrition and Health Institute of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said that overweight and obesity endanger the normal growth and development of adolescents, have adverse effects on their psychology, behavior, cognition and intelligence, and even lead to high blood pressure, high blood sugar and high blood lipids in children.
At the same time, overweight and obesity in adolescents are likely to continue into adulthood, which will increase the risk of chronic diseases such as hypertension and diabetes in adolescents.
Ding Gangqiang said that from 2010 to 2012, the nutrition and health status of Chinese residents showed that the overweight rate of children and adolescents aged 6-17 in China was 9.6%, and the obesity rate was 6.4%, which added up to 16%.
At the same time, overweight and obesity among children and adolescents are higher than girls, and urban areas are higher than those in rural areas, and the rate of overweight and obesity has increased significantly in recent decades.
How do teenagers cope with obesity?
Zhang Li, deputy director of the Scientific Fitness and Health Promotion Research Center of the State Sports Administration, pointed out that the main reason for the current obesity of adolescents is excessive caloric intake and insufficient physical activity.
For this simple obesity, we should pay attention to scientific exercise and reasonable diet control.
Zhang Li pointed out that to maintain a healthy weight, the most important concept is "cure the disease", one of the important part is the school, parents and students to carry out a full range of popular science education, universal overweight and obesity harm, improve the awareness of adolescents to prevent.
Adolescents should undergo regular physical examinations, monitor growth and development indicators such as height and weight, and detect and scientifically determine whether overweight and obesity occur in a timely manner.
For adolescents who are already overweight and obese, Ding Gangqiang recommends that in addition to actively and scientifically arranging meals and exercise, adolescents are in a special physiological stage, and should avoid using hunger or semi-hunger therapy to control and reduce weight, and must not blindly take weight loss drugs.
Facebook (FB.O) said on Friday that hackers had stolen digital login codes that gave them access to nearly 50 million user accounts, the largest ever security breach.
Facebook, which has more than 2.2 billion monthly users, said it had not yet determined whether the attackers had misused any accounts or stolen personal information.
The company also did not find the location of the hackers, nor is it certain whether the hackers targeted specific victims.
Its initial analysis revealed that it was a large-scale attack.
CEO Mark Zuckerberg called the incident "really serious" in a media conference call.
A company spokesman said his account and the account of Chief Operating Officer Sheryl Sandberg were also affected.
Facebook shares fell 2.6 percent on Friday, dragging down major Wall Street indexes.
U.S. lawmakers said Friday that the attack could heighten calls for data privacy legislation.
"This is yet another sad piece of evidence that Congress needs to take action to protect the privacy and security of social media users," Democratic Senator Mark Warner said in a statement.
Federal Trade Commission (FTC) Commissioner Rohit Chopra said on Twitter that I would like to get an answer to Reuters’ report on the security breach.
