China News Agency Yichang October 1 (Guo Xiaoying Liu Min) newly revised "Three Gorges - Gezhouba Water Conservancy Hub Navigation Dispatch Regulations" (hereinafter referred to as the "dispatching regulations") officially began to implement on October 1, the Three Gorges lift aircraft in the trial navigation after two years, officially and the lock unified dispatch.
On the first day of the implementation of the new regulations, the navigation order of the waters of the Three Gorges-Gezhouba Dam was good.
The Yangtze River Three Gorges Navigation Authority issued the first security inspection plan at 21:00 on September 30, and carried out security inspection on 160 ships, and a total of 124 ships passed the security inspection.
At 14:00 on October 1, the navigation department arranged the first transit plan after the implementation of the new regulations.
After the implementation of the new regulations, the security inspection plan is issued once a day at 9 p.m. and 21:00, and the dam plan is released once a day at 14 p.m. and 20 a.m. each day, making it easier for ships to flexibly arrange the dam plan.
The "Dispatch Regulations" have added the "classification and control" of the ship dam dispatching principle, according to the function positioning of the lock and the lift machine to clarify the dam ship priority, the lock of the short-line passenger ship adjusted to the same priority level as the demonstration ship and the integrity ship.
This is also the second anniversary of the test operation of the lift, officially with the lock unified dispatch.
The Sichuan River and Three Gorges Repository District large-scale demonstration ships and new energy power ships also entered the priority level for the first time.
At the same time, the "dispatch regulations" will be "navigation dispatch management waters" from the previous 180 kilometers of near-dam waters to Yunyang Yangtze River Bridge to the Shi Changjiang Bridge 541.8 km of water, and divided into "core waters, near-dam waters, control waters, dispatch waters".
This is conducive to the ship to choose the appropriate water to wait for the gate, reducing the backlog of dams waiting for the locks.
The "dispatching regulations" also according to the characteristics of the current ship dam crossing and waiting for the gate, put forward the declaration of the cancellation of the violation of the ship, the delay of the dam crossing for 24 hours and other integrity restrictions.
After the water storage in the Three Gorges, the navigation conditions in the reservoir area have been improved, which has promoted the rapid development of the Yangtze River shipping.
Data show that the annual cargo pass of the Three Gorges locks and Gezhouba locks increased from 34.3 million tons in 2004 to 138 million tons and 140 million tons in 2017.
In the past two years, the Three Gorges Ascendant has passed 5,767 ships, 162,200 passengers and 1,712,800 tons of cargo.
Chen Dongyuan, deputy director of the Three Gorges Navigation Authority, said that the "dispatching regulations" have a positive effect on promoting the management of good faith over the gate, maintaining the order of navigation of the two dam hubs, relieving the pressure of ships waiting for the gate in the dam area, and improving the navigation capacity.
