With the approval of Premier Li Keqiang, the State Council recently issued the Decision on Further Reducing the Catalogue of Production License Management of Industrial Products and Simplifying the Approval Process.
The "Decision" proposes to further reduce the catalogue of production licenses for industrial products, cancel the management of 14 types of industrial products production licenses, and delegate the management authority of the production license of 4 types of industrial products to the quality and technical supervision departments of the people's governments at the provincial level.
After this reform, the implementation of industrial product production license management products will be reduced from 38 categories last year to the current 24 categories.
The Decision clearly implements a simplified approval process for products in the catalogue.
The first is to change the product inspection before the certification authority organization to submit the product inspection certificate certificate certificate certificate to the product inspection and qualification report issued by the enterprise at the time of application.
Second, in addition to hazardous chemicals, the provincial people's government quality and technical supervision department (market supervision and management department) to implement the license of the product after the implementation of on-site review, the enterprise submitted the application and product inspection qualified report and made a commitment to ensure product quality and safety, after the form of review qualified can receive the production license, after the specified time to accept the on-site review.
Third, the production and operation of enterprises in the different categories of products in the production and operation of the catalog, in accordance with the principle of "one enterprise, one certificate", when applying for a new license or applying for a new license, a license letter is reviewed and issued.
The "Decision" requires all regions and relevant departments to solidly promote the work of reducing the catalogue and simplifying the approval process.
Strengthen the commitment of enterprises to publicize and post-on-site review, strengthen credit supervision and restraint means, implement the main responsibility of enterprise quality, and revoke production licenses for false promises and non-compliance with requirements.
For products that cancel the production license management of industrial products, it is necessary to effectively strengthen post-event supervision, involving public health and safety, environmental protection and other products can be converted into mandatory certification, a positive list is listed and publicized to the public, unified certification standards, reasonable reduction and certification testing projects, and the mandatory certification costs are in principle borne by the financial system at all levels.
Take support measures to encourage enterprises to carry out voluntary certification, promote the establishment of brands, and expand the market.
It is necessary to benchmark international advanced standards and promote the improvement of industrial product quality.
Give full play to the role of third-party social organizations to ensure the quality and safety of industrial products.
For products that retain the production license management of industrial products, it is necessary to improve the standard system, give full play to the advantages of industry supervision, strengthen the responsibility of "who approves and who supervises", dynamically evaluate product quality and safety risks, and timely reduce the catalog, delegate the approval authority or turn into certification management.
In September, China's comprehensive PMI increased the manufacturing PMI month-on-month decline.
According to data released by the National Bureau of Statistics of China on the 30th, in September, China's comprehensive PMI output index was 54.1%, higher than the previous month and the annual average of 0.3 and 0.1 percentage points, indicating that the production and business activities of Chinese enterprises remained generally stable.
In the same month, the manufacturing production index and the non-manufacturing business activity index, which constitute the composite PMI output index, were 53.0% and 54.9%, respectively, down one month-on-month.
Among them, China's manufacturing PMI was 50.8%, down 0.5 percentage points from the previous month.
Zhao Qinghe said that this month's manufacturing PMI has five main characteristics:
First, the manufacturing industry fundamentals are generally stable.
Among the 21 industries surveyed, the PMI of 14 industries is in the expansion range, of which the manufacturing PMI of medicine, special equipment, electrical machinery and equipment is at a high operating level of more than 53.5%, and the growth rate is faster.
Second, there is a small fluctuation between supply and demand.
The production index and the new orders index were 53.0% and 52.0 percent, respectively, down 0.3 and 0.2 percentage points from the previous month, and supply and demand continued to maintain a state of prosperity, but the expansion slowed slightly.
The new export orders index and the import index were 48.0% and 48.5%, respectively, lower than 1.4 and 0.6 percentage points in the previous month, and the prosperity fell to the lowest level in the year.
Fourth, the cost of raw material procurement has increased.
The main raw material purchase price index was 59.8%, an increase of 1.1 percentage points over the previous month, and the ex-factory price index was 54.3%, the same as the previous month, both of which were the highest in the year.
Fifth, the operation of large enterprises is stable, and the operating conditions of small enterprises continue to improve.
Large enterprises PMI was 52.1%, the same as last month, the index has been in the expansion range of 52.0% and above this year, and this month's production index and new orders index have increased month-on-month, is the main driving force for the manufacturing industry to maintain expansion; medium-sized enterprises PMI was 48.7%, lower than the previous month's 1.7 percentage points, in the contraction range; small business PMI was 50.4%, up from 0.4 percentage points in the previous month, rising for two consecutive months.
In the same month, China's non-manufacturing business activity index was 54.9%, up 0.7 percentage points from the previous month, rising for two consecutive months.
Zhao Qinghe believes that the non-manufacturing industry as a whole continues to maintain a steady and good development momentum.
The business activity index of road transportation, securities, real estate and other industries continued to be below the critical point, and the total volume of business decreased.
Nagoya, Nov 5 (Reuters) - Bank of Japan Governor Harada said on Monday the central bank was aware that a long-term implementation of ultra-loose monetary policy could squeeze the profit margins of financial institutions and destabilize the country’s banking system.
But he said the BOJ needed to maintain its massive stimulus package, given the low inflation and uncertainty in its economies abroad, while keeping a close eye on the pros and cons of its policies.
"The Bank of Japan fully recognizes that the strength of financial institutions will be increasingly affected under continued monetary easing," Kuroda said in a speech to business leaders in Nagoya.
He said that if financial institutions are more active in undertaking risks to compensate for the impact of narrowing profit margins caused by low interest rates for many years, the banking system may be turbulent in the event of a serious negative impact.
"Although these risks are not large at present, the central bank will pay close attention to the development of the situation and encourage financial institutions to take the necessary measures," he said.
Minutes of the Bank of Japan meeting, released earlier on Monday, showed that at its September meeting, the Bank of Japan’s policy committee discussed the rising cost of long-term easing.
According to the minutes, one member said that if the economy continues to expand, "the Bank of Japan will have more flexibility in policy in the future."
Another member said the committee should discuss how long the Bank of Japan could maintain stimulus, given the limitations of the policy period.
Kuroda said the Bank of Japan would assess the financial risks posed by easing, while also taking into account the uncertainty surrounding Japan's economic outlook, as Sino-U.S. trade frictions and rising protectionism could affect global demand.
"The impact of such problems on the Japanese economy is limited for the time being," Kuroda said.
"But how the problem persists, the impact on the Japanese economy is likely to be greater," he added.
"Strong monetary easing needs to be sustained, while considering the positive and negative effects in a balanced manner," Kuroda said.
While the malpractice of the radical stimulus program has increased, such as the long-term low interest rates eroding the profits of financial institutions, the low inflation has forced the Bank of Japan to maintain the program.
The Bank of Japan maintained monetary policy last month; in the face of the risks posed by the global trade war dispute, Kuroda ruled out the possibility of a recent interest rate hike.
