The Health Bureau reminded residents that between September 2017 and August 2018, those who have received the 2017-2018 influenza vaccine still need to be vaccinated with the new influenza vaccine from September 2018, because the influenza antigen content contained in the 2018-2019 Northern Hemisphere influenza vaccine has been updated, which targets the seasonal influenza influenza in the northern hemisphere 2018-2019 winter and summer 2019.
