Chen Delin, president of the HKMA, said at the legislative meeting that at the beginning of the Sino-US trade war, Hong Kong and emerging market stock indexes ran counter to the US stock index, and until the end of September and the beginning of October, the US stock market index peaked, and market sentiment began to reverse, because investors gradually realized that the trade war was also unfavorable to the United States itself.
"Change in market sentiment is a good thing, if the trade war only has a one-sided impact, it will not help to solve the problem."
But he also pointed out that "if the Sino-US trade war fails to resolve, financial market volatility will continue to rise."
In the third quarter of this year, the foreign exchange fund's equity investment loss in Hong Kong was 8% narrower than the previous quarter to HK$4.7 billion, and the overseas stock investment income increased by 172% to HK$12.8 billion; the foreign exchange loss was HK$16.2 billion, and the bond income was HK$9.7 billion, respectively, which decreased by 24% and 31% respectively, mainly reflecting the general rise of the US dollar against major currencies in the quarter and the US interest rate in mid-September.
The Exchange Fund is mainly used to support the Hong Kong dollar.
Since 1983, Hong Kong has implemented a linked exchange rate system for the pegging of the Hong Kong dollar to the US dollar.
For the current financial situation in Hong Kong, Chen Delin said that the economic and asset market uncertainty has increased, and the downside risks have increased, but Hong Kong's financial system is stable, it is also well-defended and has sufficient earthquake resistance.
"Hong Kong's international investment position is abundant, with an external net asset value of $1.4 trillion, equivalent to four times of GDP, higher than Singapore's 2.5 times and Japan's 0.6 times, to cope with the economic downturn or reverse enough."
Recently, the Hong Kong dollar interest rate continued to fall and expand with the US dollar spread, Chen Delin pointed out that the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate on September 21 once rose more than 400 basis points, the market is generally believed to be mainly related to the Hong Kong dollar interest rate increase, after the Hong Kong dollar against the dollar around the level of 7.80-7.84, to the recent Hong Kong dollar interest rate continued to fall, and the dollar spread expanded, may attract the market to Hong Kong dollar, buy the dollar interest rate increase, so that the Hong Kong dollar again.
However, he believes that with the start of the Hong Kong Bank interest rate hike cycle and the normalization of the Hong Kong dollar interest rate, the situation of the Hong Kong dollar interest rate lower than the US dollar interest rate will change in the future.
"The Hong Kong dollar interest rate and the US dollar interest rate trend will be more consistent, we must be more careful to manage the risk, be prepared to cope with market fluctuations."
Due to the abundant funds of the Hong Kong dollar, the Hong Kong dollar interest rate reduction further fell, the three-month interest rate cut fell by 0.9% to 2.08179 % on Monday, and the spread with the US dollar was widened from 46 basis points to 51 basis points; the one-month interest rate cut was a five-month low, and the interest rate difference with the US dollar was expanded from 120 basis points to 127 basis points.
From May to mid-September, the Hong Kong dollar spot exchange rate was close to 7.85 to the dollar for most of the time.
During the period, due to factors such as the outflow of some of the funds from the Hong Kong dollar after the completion of the carry activity and the large-scale prospectus, the weak party exchange guarantee was triggered many times in May and August after the first time was triggered in April.
The HKMA bought Hong Kong dollars and exported US dollars at the 7.85 level in accordance with the linked exchange rate system to maintain the stability of the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate.
The HKMA bought a total of approximately HK$52.1 billion in May and August under the Weak Party Exchange Assurance Mechanism.
Is there any interest in the new tax law for foreigners?
The relevant person in charge of the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation said in response to a reporter's question on the 30th that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step in the implementation of the new personal income tax law will consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for overseas people, including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
A reporter asked, the newly revised personal income tax law will adjust the criteria for the determination of China's personal income tax resident taxpayers from one year to 183 days.
When implementing the law in the next step, will there be preferential arrangements for overseas persons, including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan?
The person in charge responded that the current implementing regulations of the Individual Income Tax Law have special preferential provisions on the payment of taxes for overseas persons, and individuals who do not have residence in China but have lived for more than one year or less than one year or less can receive income from outside China and may only pay personal income tax on the part paid by units or individuals in China.
The person in charge said that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step in the implementation of the new personal income tax law will consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for overseas persons, including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
There is no "threshold" moon child center: quality certification promotes quality improvement.
With the pull of the "two-child economy" and the prosperity of the mother and baby market, from the north to the third and fourth tier cities, various grades of moon clubs have sprung up.
At present, the hot moon club meets the consumption needs of the masses, and charges range from tens of thousands of yuan to hundreds of thousands of yuan, but it is also in an embarrassing situation, this institution has no threshold so far, and there is still a blank area of supervision.
The State Administration of Market Supervision recently launched the 2018 National "Quality Month" series of activities, and the reporter came to a five-star monthly center in Tianjin to visit the experience of maternal and child care service certification.
The general monthly children's center provides neonatal care, nutrition meals, postpartum repair and other services.
In this lunar center, the reporter saw that the nurse checked the breastfeeding situation of newborns every day, and professional carers provided fine care services such as bathing and touching for newborns.
At the same time, in order to meet the needs of new mothers, from the initial wound care of the moon to the beauty care and other services in the middle and late moon, medical treatment and beauty care programs are provided to help mothers restore their posture.
A new mother who lives in the house told reporters that she had booked the clubhouse eight months in advance.
The service items of the monthly club directly affect the comfort level and physical recovery during the maternal month, and some small-scale monthly club can only provide some simple monthly services, and there are hidden problems such as irregular disinfection hygiene, easy cross-infection, and single unscientific diet.
The head of the Yuezi Center said that they are the only one of all five-star children's centers in Tianjin to have obtained B-level service certification.
"Although some customers do not understand the meaning of B-level certification at first, but through certification forced enterprises to strictly standardize the process management, so that customers benefit, the long-term development of the enterprise is of great significance," he said.
Pan Lifen, deputy director of the certification supervision department of the State Administration of Market Supervision, said that service certification is a new type of certification system based on customer perception, paying attention to the degree of organizational quality management and service characteristics, which is an important part of the national quality infrastructure, and plays a positive role in improving the proportion of high-quality service supply and enhancing the international competitiveness of China's services.
China started from 2004, after more than 10 years of development, service certification project has experienced from scratch, gradual development process, the emergence of such as financial services certification, maternal and child care service certification, commodity after-sales service certification, e-commerce service certification, health service certification and a number of service certification have a certain influence.
According to the statistics of the State Administration of Market Supervision, there are more than 130 service certification bodies in China, more than 2,000 service certification personnel, and nearly 8,000 valid certification certificates.
Pan Lifen said that it is necessary to further guide and promote the development of service certification, gradually expand service certification coverage in the fields of health, education, sports, finance, and e-commerce, and promote the supply-side reform and quality improvement of the service industry.
HONG KONG, Nov 5 (Reuters) - Hong Kong property prices fell for two consecutive months after peaking, and Hong Kong Monetary Authority President Chen Delin said on Monday that fashion needs time to observe whether the property market has entered a downward cycle, and if confirmed, it can consider easing the tightening of counter-cyclical measures in due course.
Chen Delin also pointed out that if the property price correction, the first to be affected will be those who buy a home at the peak of the property market, but it is expected that the opportunity for property prices to fall sharply during the Asian financial crisis in 1997, and the public will sell the property significantly.
Chen Delin led a number of senior officials of the HKMA to attend the Legislative Council briefing, saying that if it is confirmed that the property market has entered a downward cycle, measures can be relaxed in due course.
"But now only a few weeks of data, relaxation is still too early, there is still more time to see whether the property market has entered the downward cycle."
Since the 10th of 2009, the HKMA has launched eight rounds of counter-cyclical measures to significantly tighten the mortgages of various properties, including reducing the number of mortgages and the need for mortgage applicants to pass rigorous stress tests to improve bank risk management and earthquake resistance.
As Hong Kong officially entered the rate hike cycle, the Hong Kong private residential property price index peaked for two consecutive months in August-September, and the monthly decline in September expanded to 1.44%.
However, the cumulative increase in the first three quarters of this year still reached 10.2%.
In the second quarter of this year, the proportion of households living in Hong Kong without mortgages reached 66%, up from an average of 60% in 2009-11, compared with an average of 60% in 2009-11; the contribution-to-income ratio of newly approved mortgages and newly approved mortgages was 47% and 34%, respectively, compared with 64% and 41% in 2009-11.
However, Chen Delin said that the high seismic capacity does not mean that the citizens who have already bought the property will not be damaged by the economic downturn, because the valuation of the property will fall, and those who buy buildings at the peak will bear the brunt.
Although the HKMA has tightened bank lending to mortgage lenders, homebuyers can also obtain high-volume mortgage loans through mortgage insurance or mortgage loans provided by developers.
Chen Delin said that at present, together with the mortgage loans provided to developers, the mortgage ratio of borrowers can reach 85-90%, and if the property price falls by 10%, there will be negative assets (that is, the market value of the property will fall below the level of the total amount of outstanding mortgage loans).
However, Nguyen Guo Heng, vice president of the HKMA, pointed out that the authorities estimate that the total number of mortgages provided by developers accounts for only 2-2.5% of the total number of mortgages in banks, and the proportion is still low.
At the peak of negative assets in Hong Kong in 2003, the number of negative assets exceeded 100,000, accounting for 22% of the number of people providing for buildings.
As of the third quarter of this year, Hong Kong recorded zero negative assets for seven consecutive quarters.
