The sinking of an illegal immigrant boat in Turkey's Aegean Sea killed five people.
ISTANBUL, Sept. 30 (Xinhua) -- According to Turkish media reports on the 30th, an inflatable boat carrying illegal immigrants capsized in the waters of the Aegean Sea in Turkey on the same day, killing at least five people.
The inflatable boat, which was scheduled to travel to an island in Greece, sank near the Enez area in Edirne province in northwestern Turkey on the same day, and the reason for the sinking was unknown.
It is unclear how many illegal immigrants were on board the sinking inflatable.
Because it is estimated that there are still people trapped in the sea, the relevant search and rescue operations continue.
The Aegean Sea was once the preferred route for illegal immigrants to cross the continent via Turkey.
After Turkey controlled it under the agreement signed with the European Union in March 2016, the number of people smuggled through this channel has been greatly reduced.
But this year, the number of people smuggled on this channel has rebounded again.
