From November 1, China will reduce the most-favoured-nation tax rate for some commodities, and the total tariff level will be reduced to 7.5%.
According to the decision of the 26th executive meeting of the State Council, the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council issued a notice on the 30th to reduce the most-favoured nation tax rate for some commodities from November 1, 2018.
According to the "Announcement of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council on Reducing Import Tariffs on Some Commodities", in order to adapt to industrial upgrading, reduce corporate costs and meet the needs of the multi-level consumption of the masses, the most-favoured-nation tax rate for some industrial goods and other commodities will be reduced from November 1 this year.
The total number of tax items reduced is 1,585, accounting for about 19% of the total number of tax items in China, and the average tax rate is reduced from 10.5% to 7.8%, and the average reduction is 26%.
The tax reduction mainly involves textiles; stone, ceramics, glass products; some steel and base metal products; electromechanical equipment and parts, such as metal processing machinery, textile machinery, construction machinery, power transmission and transformation equipment, electrical equipment, instrumentation, etc.; resource commodities and primary processed products, such as non-metallic minerals, inorganic chemicals, wood and paper products, precious jade and so on.
At the same time, with the reduction of the overall tariff level, especially the import tariffs on drugs and consumer goods, the tax rate of import duties on imported goods will be reduced accordingly.
In order to implement the decision-making and deployment of the Party Central Committee and the State Council, China has implemented zero tariffs on the vast majority of imported drugs since May 1 this year, reduced import tariffs on automobiles and parts and some consumer goods since July 1, and implemented the third step of the information technology agreement to reduce taxes.
The reporter learned from the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council that since this year, after many consecutive independent adjustments, the overall level of tariffs in China will be reduced from 9.8% last year to 7.5%, with an average decline of 23%.
The appropriate reduction of tariffs is conducive to promoting the balanced development of foreign trade, promoting a higher level of opening up, and making overall use of both international and domestic resources to promote domestic supply-side structural reform.
The relevant person in charge of the committee said that this year is the 40th anniversary of reform and opening up, and taking the initiative to reduce the overall level of tariffs is the practical action to implement the spirit of General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speech at the Boao Forum for Asia, and it is also an important measure for China to further expand opening up and actively expand imports according to its own high-quality development needs.
