The first joint visit of the Han River into the mouth of the Han River by the ROK in 65 years
The South Korean Ministry of National Defense confirmed on the 5th that the ROK and the DPRK launched a joint inspection of the waters of the Han and Linjin Rivers into the sea on the same day.
The initiative is in preparation for the free navigation of civilian vessels on both sides.
According to the notice provided to the media by the South Korean Ministry of National Defense on the same day, this is the first joint inspection of the Han River into the sea since the signing of the Korean War Armistice Agreement in 1953.
The ROK and the DPRK signed a military agreement in September this year, agreeing to jointly visit waters such as the Han River into the mouth of the sea from November to ensure environmental protection and development of the waters in the future.
In October, the two Koreas planned a joint study of the waters at a general-level meeting.
On November 5, the joint investigation of inter-Korean waters was officially launched.
The joint delegation consisted of 20 people from the ROK military and experts.
According to the South Korean Ministry of National Defense, during the visit, personnel from both sides did not carry weapons and prohibited the use of words and deeds that stimulated each other.
"Because there is no military demarcation line near the entrance to the sea, the area was once a high-incident area, but through joint inspection, the future here will become a new peace area."
The waters jointly visited by the ROK and the DPRK are about 70 kilometers long and have a total area of about 280 square kilometers.
According to the South Korean Ministry of National Defense, the South Korean side will send six research vessels to detect the depth of the seawater and so on, providing basic information for the safe navigation of the waters; after the completion of the investigation, it will provide navigation maps for the exchange of civilian ships.
The two Koreas held a summit meeting in Pyongyang in October 2007 to reach an agreement on jointly using the Han and Linjin rivers into the mouth of the sea, but subsequent negotiations were stranded due to tensions on the peninsula.
According to the military agreement signed by the two Koreas in September, in the future, ships of the two sides need to inform each other in advance before sailing in common waters.
According to the website of the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia on the 4th, recently, Chinese citizens Guo Yuqin and Mao Runxin lost contact during their tourism in Mongolia.
It is understood that the two are members of the blue sky rescue team, on October 19, the two contacted relatives and friends in the country, said that they would soon enter the mountain near Kusugur Lake to explore, and shared their location through WeChat, after which they lost contact, suspected of having gone to no-man's land.
The Chinese Embassy in Mongolia has always attached great importance to protecting the legitimate rights and interests of Chinese citizens in Mongolia, and to consular protection and assistance.
After learning the news of the loss of contact between the two tourists, the embassy immediately launched the emergency plan for consular protection, and strived to seize the golden rescue time and work hard.
The Embassy maintains close communication with the family members, assists the family to report the case to the Mongolian police immediately, and provides the family with a translation list for selection.
The Embassy immediately met with the heads of the Ministry of External Relations of Mongolia, the General Administration of Police and the General Administration of Emergency Situations, informed the relevant situation, asked the Mongolian side to carry out search and rescue as soon as possible, and maintain close communication with the Mongolian side throughout the search and rescue process to ensure timely grasp of the latest progress.
At the same time, the Embassy assisted the family to issue a search notice in Mongolia, and widely mobilized overseas Chinese and Chinese-funded enterprises to actively participate in the search for people, provided effective clues, and provided relevant assistance to a number of blue sky rescue team members who went to Mongolia to assist in rescue.
Under the strong promotion of the Embassy, the Mongolian side sent a rescue team for the first time and promised to exempt the cost of search and rescue.
The General Directorate of the Mon Police and the General Directorate of Emergency Situations instructed the police and emergency services of Kusugur Province to make every effort to search and rescue.
Because Kusugur Lake is located in the northern part of Mongolia and Russia, it is remote, sparsely populated, and transportation and communication are extremely inconvenient, and at present, Mongolia has entered a severe winter, the temperature is as low as minus 20 degrees, the local police and emergency departments have overcome great difficulties, mobilized almost all police forces, and mobilized local herders, through horseback riding, walking, visiting herdsmen, etc., in a wide range of carpet search and rescue around the two people lost contact.
At the same time, in view of the special situation of the pastoral area, the Mongolian side has been publishing people's notices through the radio cycle for many days.
The relevant staff of the domestic blue sky rescue team have also come to Mongolia and Mongolia to actively participate in the rescue.
The safety of the two missing people has always touched our hearts.
So far, the two have been missing for more than 10 days, and the embassy has received some clues, but the two have not been found, and the search and rescue operation is still under intense.
The Embassy will always pay attention to this matter in accordance with the principle of "people-oriented", promote the Mongolian side to continue to make full efforts to search and rescue, and provide maximum assistance to the families of the parties concerned.
The Embassy calls on compatriots and enterprises in Mongolia, if they learn relevant clues, please contact the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia at the first time.
